name: Yolk sac 10x scRNA-seq data
desc:
A scRNA-seq dataset containing our yolk sac scRNA-seq data (10x;  n=10 , k=169,798; 4-8 post-conception weeks).
Yolk sac 10x scRNA-seq data - E-MTAB-10552. Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: Integrated multi-organ progenitors 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing HSPCs/HSCs across multiple tissues datasets including Yolksac, AGM, Liver, Bone marrow, Skin, Definitive iPSC-HSPCs and iPSC-HSPCs, n=29, k=5008. Annotations also available in supplementary tables.
tissue: Yolk Sac,  AGM, Liver, Bone marrow, Skin, iPSC-HSPCs(Definitive), iPSC_derived-HSPCs

name: Yolk sac pre-AGM Myeloid lineage 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing our yolk sac scRNA-seq data subset to Myeloid lineages arising prior to Carnegie Stage 14 (10x; n=2, k=3389; 3-4 post-conception weeks)  - E-MTAB-10552. Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: Yolk sac post-AGM Myeloid lineage 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing our yolk sac scRNA-seq data subset to Myeloid lineages arising post Carnegie Stage 14 (10x; n=6, k=6291; 5-8 post-conception weeks)  - E-MTAB-10552. Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: Yolk sac HSPC trajectory 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing our yolk sac scRNA-seq data subset to the trajectory transition between Hemogenic endothelium and HSPC cellstates (10X; n=3, k=2262; 4-6 post-conception weeks) - E-MTAB-10552.  Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: Embryonic Liver 10x scRNA-seq data
desc:
A scRNA-seq dataset containing our embryonic Liver scRNA-seq data with matched donors to the Yolksac dataset (10x;  n=3, k=49376; 4-8 post-conception weeks).
Yolk sac 10x scRNA-seq data - E-MTAB-10552. Annotations also available in supplementary tables. Embryonic Liver scRNA-seq (10x) dataset, n=3, k=49376. Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: Yolk sac and embryonic liver 10x scRNA-seq data combined
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing combined data for our yolk sac scRNA-seq data (10x; n=8, k=134,765; 5-8 post-conception weeks)  - E-MTAB-10552. Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: Mouse gastrulation data (10x) - haematopoietic lineages only
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing Mouse gastrulation scRNA-seq data subset to Haematopoietic lineage (10x; n=28, k=4717; E6-E9.5). Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: iPSC data (Definitive) - AEC-HSPC trajectory 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing data from the iPSC culture system from the Mikola lab subset to the Myeloid lineage trajectory(10x; n=5, k=552; https://doi.org/10.1101/2021.11.17.469005). Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: iPSC data (Primitive) - AEC-HSPC trajectory 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing data from the iPSC culture system from the Vento lab subset to the transition trajectory between AEC and HSPCs (10x; n=6, k=368; https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-022-04571-x). Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: iPSC data - myeloid monocyte independent trajectory 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing data from the iPSC culture system from the Vento lab subset to the transition trajectory between AEC and HSPCs (10x; n=5, k=552; https://doi.org/10.1101/2021.11.17.469005). Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: iPSC data - myeloid monocyte dependent trajectory 10x scRNA-seq data
desc: A scRNA-seq dataset containing data from the iPSC culture system from the Vento lab subset to the transition trajectory between AEC and HSPCs (10x; n=7, k=7676; https://doi.org/10.1101/2021.11.17.469005). Annotations also available in supplementary tables.

name: Yolk sac CITE-seq data (protein and RNA combined)
desc: A CITE-seq dataset containing protein and RNA data hstacked for our yolk sac CITE-seq data (n=2, k=3,559, Carnegie stage 16-19). One half of the data has undergone CD34+ enrichment, and the other half has undergone CD34- enrichment via FACS. Yolk sac CITE-seq data - E-MTAB-11549

name: Yolk sac CITE-seq data (protein)
desc: A CITE-seq dataset containing protein for our yolk sac CITE-seq data (n=2, k=3,559, Carnegie stage 16-19). One half of the data has undergone CD34+ enrichment, and the other half has undergone CD34- enrichment via FACS. Yolk sac CITE-seq data - E-MTAB-11549

name: Yolk sac CITE-seq data (RNA)
desc: A CITE-seq dataset containing RNA data for our yolk sac CITE-seq data (n=2, k=3,559, Carnegie stage 16-19). One half of the data has undergone CD34+ enrichment, and the other half has undergone CD34- enrichment via FACS. An additional number of cells (k=4,061) are present in the portal compared with the manuscript figures, since all post-QC RNA data are shown, rather than just those with intersect with protein component. Yolk sac CITE-seq data - E-MTAB-11549

name: Embryonic liver CITE-seq data (protein and RNA combined)
desc: A CITE-seq dataset containing protein and RNA data hstacked for our embryonic liver CITE-seq data (n=2, k=7,739, Carnegie stage 16-19). One lane of the data has undergone CD34+ enrichment, and two lanes have undergone CD34- enrichment via FACS. Embryonic liver CITE-seq data - E-MTAB-11618

name: Embryonic liver CITE-seq data (protein)
desc: A CITE-seq dataset containing protein data for our embryonic liver CITE-seq data (n=2, k=7,739, Carnegie stage 16-19). One lane of the data has undergone CD34+ enrichment, and two lanes have undergone CD34- enrichment via FACS. Embryonic liver CITE-seq data - E-MTAB-11618

name: Embryonic liver CITE-seq data (RNA)
desc: A CITE-seq dataset containing RNA data for our embryonic liver CITE-seq data (n=2, k=7,739, Carnegie stage 16-19). One lane of the data has undergone CD34+ enrichment, and two lanes have undergone CD34- enrichment via FACS. An additional number of cells (k=9,679) are present in the portal compared with the manuscript figures, since all post-QC RNA data are shown, rather than just those with intersect with protein component. Embryonic liver CITE-seq data - E-MTAB-11618

name: Supplementary tables
desc: Supplementary tables containing supplementary data for our manuscript Multi-organ functions of yolk sac during human early development including annotations, statistical results, differentially expressed genes and logistic regression probabilities.

desc: Light sheet microscopy of Yolk sac at 6.9 PCW including markers CD34, ECAD and LYVE1

name: Video (PLVAP, IBA1 and LYVE1)
desc: Light sheet microscopy of Yolk sac at 6.9 PCW including markers PLVAP, IBA1 and LYVE1

name: microglia_LR_model_YS_brain_20220404.sav
desc: Celltypist compatible logistic regression model trained between combined low-dimensional LDVAE latent representations of our YS dataset integrated with the Eze etal fetal Brain data (https://doi.org/10.1038/s41593-020-00794-1) and used for classification harmonisation between datasets

name: microglia_LR_model_YS_skin_20220404.sav
desc: Celltypist compatible logistic regression model trained between combined low-dimensional LDVAE latent representations of our YS dataset integrated with the Suo etal fetal Skin data (https://doi.org/10.1101/2022.01.17.476665) and used for classification harmonisation between datasets

name: gonad_model_20220617.sav
desc: Celltypist compatible logistic regression model trained between combined low-dimensional LDVAE latent representations of our YS dataset integrated with the Luz etal fetal Gonads data (https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-022-04918-4) and used for classification harmonisation between datasets

name: EC_liver_model.sav
desc: Celltypist compatible logistic regression model trained between combined low-dimensional LDVAE latent representations of our YS dataset integrated with our matched liver single cell scRNA-seq data and used for classification harmonisation between datasets

name: EC_FBM_model.sav
desc: Celltypist compatible logistic regression model trained between combined low-dimensional LDVAE latent representations of our YS dataset integrated with the Jardine etal Fetal Bone marrow data (https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-021-03929-x) and used for classification harmonisation between datasets
